INSERT INTO `faqs` (`pkey`, `question`, `answer`, `category`) VALUES (1,'How do I learn to use my machine?','Set-up and operating instructions, parts manuals, and a technical guide can be found online at merrow.com.  Merrow also has a worldwide network of distributors who are able to help you learn to use your machine.','Technology'),(2,'How often should I oil my machine?','Merrow 70-class, M-class and MG-class machines are self-oiling.  Maintain a full oil reservoir and check the bubbler cap to confirm that the oil system is working correctly.  Merrow High Arm machines should be oiled after the machine becomes louder than normal and before use when the machine has not been used for an extended period.','Technology'),(3,'What routine maintenance is required for my machine?','Remove debris from moving parts. Excess thread and fabric will induce rust, wear and generally decreased machine life. With machine off, check that the needle carrier has no lateral motion. Grab the top of the needle carrier and try to wiggle the carrier from right to left.','Technology'),(4,'Where can I find replacement parts?','Merrow stocks and sells replacement parts for all of our machines.  Please order your replacement parts from Merrow.  Machines fitted with generic parts are not covered by our warranty.','Sales'),(5,'Where can I service my machine?','Please contact Merrow for a list of authorized service providers in your area.  ','General'),(6,'What type of warranty does Merrow offer?','Merrow machines all come with a 30 day guarantee and one-year warranty, voided if machine is serviced by unauthorized dealers or if generic replacement parts are used.','Sales'),(7,'What types of installations are compatible with Merrow machines?','All Merrow machines are compatible with the Merrow Ziggurat table and other tables.  Our 70-class and some other machines are compatible with rail and fully automated systems.  See our OEM guide.','Technology'),(8,'What motors are used with Merrow machines?','Merrow machines are compatible with both air and electric motors.  Motors are sold separately.','Technology'),(9,'Where does Merrow ship to?','Merrow ships worldwide via UPS, Fedex, DHL and private carrier.  Shipments go out daily from Massachusetts, USA.  All shipments are insured.','Sales'),(10,'What components come standard with the machines?','Merrow ships its machines with the following components, a value of $150 USD: Thread stand assembly, set-up manual, instruction manual, tweezers, motor chain, feed eccentric wrench, nut driver, eccentric extractor, sample needles, looper bender and spare nuts and bolts.','Sales'),(11,'Are Merrow machines manufactured in the USA?','Yes, Merrow machines are manufactured in Wareham, Massachusetts, USA.  We are the only American sewing machine company still operating in the US.','General'),(12,'How are Merrow machines different from other sewing machines?','Merrow sewing machines are unique because they are the only machines run by a cam-based system.  This cam-based system is superior because it produces a more reliable, more precise stitch than the competition.','Quality'),(13,'How long do Merrow machines last?','Merrow machines can last up to 60 years in the factory environment with minimal maintenance.  Of course, basic care and occasional replacement of parts is necessary to keep your machine running in optimal condition. ','Quality'),(14,'What is a cam-based sewing system?','Two barrel cams sit on top of each other, manufactured to extremely precise tolerances.  Each cam has a track or seriws of track that a \'cam roll\' will follow.  These tracks determine the motion of the needle and loopers to .001 mm.  Nothing can beat the accuracy of a cam system.  Our cam-driven machines produce a superior quality stitch when compared to any sewing machine in the industry.  Using sophisticated 5-axis milling machines, we\'ve suceeded in developing proprietary high-technology components offering faster, quieter operation and solid durability.','Technology'),(15,'What technical advantages does a cam-based system allow in the real world?','From the finest silk to the toughest leather, even fiberglass, Merrow has a precision feeding and stitching solution for your most demanding material processing requirements.  We\'ll customize our machines to meet your current challenges or pursue entirely new applications.','Technology'),(16,'What is your return policy?','Machines can be returned, unused, within 30 days.  Parts may not be returned unless defective.','Administration'),(17,'Where can I find information about parts and accessories?','Merrow offers more than 10,000 genuine parts for machines.  Our parts guides should help you find whatever you need.  Please call us for more help.','Administration'),(18,'Can I link my business to Merrow.com?','To protect Merrow\'s trademark rights, it is critically important that everyone, including people who link to Merrow web sites, use the company\'s trade names and trademarks correctly and consistently.  ','Marketing'),(19,'Whom should I contact about Invoice payment, Billing and Purchase order questions?','Please call 508.295.8899 and request to speak with sales.  Or login to your account onlin.','Sales'),(20,'Where can I find information about a particular sewing machine?','Please look up the model online, we have extensive information available which describes each machine and its capabilities.  Or call 508.295.8899 and request to speak with sales.','Sales'),(21,'When can I expect delivery if I order online?','Your order will be processed with the same attention as if you were to call or fax it in.  Please login to your account for an update.','Sales'),(22,'How do I get information about a former Merrow product?','Just ask - usually we can help.','General');
